The paper deals with the distribution of mutual information in MIMO channels, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and communication systems (cs.COMM). The use of OFDM and spatial multiplexing also suggests a possible connection to signal processing (cs.SY) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the mention of antennas and channels indicates a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM).
